      "span_text": "This would be yet another case where Kv4.2 and AMPARs are anti-regulated. Chemically and synaptically evoked LTP both induce GluR1 AMPAR insertion, which is coincident with Kv4.2 internalization (Shi et al., 1999; [CITATION_1] . Additionally, the Ht31 peptide, which we found to increase Kv4.2 expression, acts to decrease GluR1 surface expression [CITATION_2] , suggesting possible coregulation of Kv4.2 and AMPAR trafficking during LTP."
